Sources of information on treatment of smallpox cases
-----------------------------------------------------
Interesting hypothesis and questions. A possible resource would be the
Chemical Casualty Care Division, US Army Medical Research Institute of
Chemical Defense, Aberdeen, MD. Their website is accessible at
<http://ccc.apgea.army.mil>. From there, go to their contact link. They
work directly with the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) on
many of these issues and may be able to help answer these questions.
Another resource is the CDC Emergency Preparedness and Response Cell
Emergency Operations Div, phone number 770 488 7100. This is a 24hr number.
--
Bruce Jeffries, Maj, USAF, BSC (PA-C)
Joint Regional Medical Planner, US Joint Forces Command
Ft McPherson, GA FEMA Region IV
<Bruce.Jeffries@forscom.army.mil>
